title: Week 6 honor roll: Bilal Ally headlines top performers
text:
Week 6 honor roll: Bilal Ally headlines top performers 
By Justin Barney Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 9:11 pm Photos Gary McCullough/For the Times-Union Clay's Bilal Ally, shown here in the 2013 state title game, rushed for an area-high 396 yards and seven touchdowns last week in a win over Menendez. 
A glance at the area's top high school football performances in Week 6. 
Bilal Ally, RB, Clay: Carried 34 times for a school-record 396 yards and seven TDs in a 53-35 win over Menendez. That total is the area’s highest this season. 
Keylan Brown, RB, Oakleaf: Accounted for 22 of the Knights’ 30 points in a 30-16 win over Fleming Island. Had 223 rushing yards and three TDs, and added a pair of two-point conversion runs. 
Billy Cobb, QB, Trinity Christian: Was 12-of-13 passing for 236 yards and three TDs in the Conquerors 43-0 win over Providence. 
Tron McCarter, ATH, Cedar Creek Christian: Scored three touchdowns — on a 96-yard run, a 61-yard interception return and a 19-yard reception — in a 54-12 win over Eagle’s View. 
Nick Tronti, QB, Ponte Vedra: Accounted for six TDs (four passing, two rushing) in a 48-25 win over Westside. He finished 17-of-19 passing for 262 yards. 
Isaiah Westbrook, WR, Bolles: Had two receiving TDs, one rushing score and added a 90-yard kickoff return for a TD in a 56-6 win over West Nassau. 
Logan Wright, RB, Sandalwood: Rushed for 170 yards and all three Sandalwood TDs on 30 carries in a 21-7 win over Flagler Palm Coast. 
Note: Coaches can submit their weekly honor roll nominations to preps@jacksonville.com
